((3) 0 () 0 () () (u . "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <meta name=\"format-detection\" content=\"telephone=no\">\n\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/functions.js\"></script>\n\n  <meta content=\"Research & Writing | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" name=\"title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori's research, writing, and publications.\" name=\"description\" />\n  <meta content=\"website\" property=\"og:type\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/research.html\" property=\"og:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Research & Writing | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"og:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori's research, writing, and publications.\" property=\"og:description\" />\n  <meta content=\"summary_large_image\" property=\"twitter:card\" />\n  <meta content=\"@xandernn\" property=\"twitter:site\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/research.html\" property=\"twitter:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Research & Writing | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"twitter:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori's research, writing, and publications.\" property=\"twitter:description\" />\n\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/fonts/fonts.css\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/styles.css\" />\n\n  <title>Research & Writing | Alexander Nabavi-Noori</title>\n\n  <style type=\"text/css\">\n    #switcher {\n      margin-top: 12px;\n      border: 1px solid gray;\n      box-shadow: 2px 2px;\n      cursor: default;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding-top: 0.2em;\n      padding-bottom: 0.2em;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n\n<body id=\"body\" class=\"body-text_century-supra\">\n\n  <div id=\"switcher\"><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"about.html\">About</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link active\" href=\"research.html\">Research</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"experience.html\">Experience</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"blog.html\">Blog</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"cv.html\">CV</a>\n</div>\n\n  <div id=\"content\">\n\n    <div id=\"doc\"><div id=\"doc\"><p><title-block><topic class=\"small\">Research &amp; Writ\u00ADing</topic><short-rule></short-rule></title-block></p><div class=\"subhead\" id=\"research\"><a href=\"#research\">Aca\u00ADd\u00ADe\u00ADmic Pub\u00ADli\u00ADca\u00ADtions</a></div><p><a href=\"https://yalelawjournal.org/index.php/article/agency-control-and-internally-binding-norms\"><book>Agency Con\u00ADtrol and Inter\u00ADnally Bind\u00ADing Norms,</book></a> 131 <sc>Yale L.J.</sc> 1278 (2022) (Note)</p><div class=\"indented\">Courts can’t agree on whether agency guid\u00ADance can bind the agency itself—this Note shows why it must and pro\u00ADposes a new frame\u00ADwork for judi\u00ADcial review.</div><p><a href=\"https://scholarship.law.duke.edu/dlj/vol69/iss7/2/\"><book>Toward a Demo\u00ADspru\u00ADdence of Poverty,</book></a>, 69 <sc>Duke L.J.</sc> 1473 (2020) (co-authored with Mon\u00ADica C. Bell and Stephanie Gar\u00ADlock)</p><div class=\"indented\">Courts treat poverty crim\u00ADi\u00ADnal\u00ADiza\u00ADtion as a prob\u00ADlem of process—inad\u00ADe\u00ADquate hear\u00ADings, exces\u00ADsive bail. But poverty is crim\u00ADi\u00ADnal\u00ADized long before any\u00ADone enters a court\u00ADroom. This Arti\u00ADcle pro\u00ADposes that judges learn from poor com\u00ADmu\u00ADni\u00ADties and use their full toolkit to make that struc\u00ADtural real\u00ADity vis\u00ADi\u00ADble.</div><p><a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33404318/\"><book>Gun Vio\u00ADlence in Court,</book></a>, 48 <sc>J. Law, Med. &amp; Ethics</sc> 90 (2020) (co-authored with Abbe R. Gluck and Susan Wang)</p><div class=\"indented\">Lit\u00ADi\u00ADga\u00ADtion has dri\u00ADven change from tobacco to opi\u00ADoids, but the gun indus\u00ADtry remains uniquely shielded. This paper sur\u00ADveys firearm suits and finds major pub\u00ADlic lit\u00ADi\u00ADga\u00ADtion efforts con\u00ADspic\u00ADu\u00ADously absent.</div></div></div><a id=\"links\"></a>\n    <div class=\"gap\" style=\"height:1em\"></div>\n    <ul class=\"children\"></ul>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"toolbar\" class=\"\">\n\n    <div id=\"navtable\">\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"colophon.html\"><span class=\"arrow\">←</span>&nbsp;colophon</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"center\">\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/\">home</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/cv.pdf\">curriculum vitae&nbsp;<span class=\"arrow\">→</span></a>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n</body>\n\n</html>"))